rescue operations are under way after a 6 . 1 magnitude earthquake hit indonesia's aceh province , flattening houses and causing landslides .
officials say at least 24 people were killed and more than 200 injured by the quake , which struck the western tip of sumatra island on tuesday .
one report said six children were killed and 14 trapped under debris when a mosque collapsed in central aceh .
indonesia is located on one of the most seismically active regions on earth .
"we have recorded 24 people dead and 249 people injured , " disaster agency spokesman sutopo purwo nugroho told agence - france presse ( afp ) news agency .
he added that more than 300 buildings have been damaged in the quake .
